  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Multi-organ failure due to sepsis is a major cause of death in critically ill patients. But&#xD;
      the mechanisms leading to this condition are not fully understood. Mitochondrial dysfunction&#xD;
      has been shown in skeletal muscle of critically ill septic patients. Liver is very important&#xD;
      in sepsis as it is responsible of the synthesis of several inflammatory proteins. Moreover&#xD;
      hepatic failure is associated to a bad outcome.&#xD;
&#xD;
      The aim of this study is to evaluate the hepatic mitochondrial function in sepsis.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
